# MVNO Cell Service

> Concept for a Mobile Virtual Network Operator - reselling cellular service with a unique angle.

---

## Executive Summary

An **MVNO (Mobile Virtual Network Operator)** is a wireless carrier that doesn't own network infrastructure but instead purchases wholesale access from major carriers and resells it under their own brand.

**Status:** Early concept requiring significant capital and expertise. This document provides comprehensive research for informed decision-making.

**Bottom Line Assessment:**

| Factor | Rating | Notes |
|--------|--------|-------|
| Market Opportunity | Medium | $30B+ US market, growing 7.5% CAGR |
| Capital Required | Very High | $100K-$2M+ for proper launch |
| Expertise Required | Very High | Telecom regulatory + technical |
| Fit with Other Ventures | Medium | Synergies exist but not core strength |
| Risk Level | High | Thin margins, intense competition |
| **Recommendation** | **Low Priority** | Explore alternatives first |

