## Successful MVNO Case Studies

### Mint Mobile (T-Mobile)

**Strategy:** Direct-to-consumer, digital-only, aggressive pricing, celebrity marketing (Ryan Reynolds)

**Key Success Factors:**
- Eliminated retail overhead
- Viral marketing campaigns
- Simple, transparent pricing
- Prepaid model (no credit risk)

**Outcome:** Acquired by T-Mobile for $1.35 billion (2023)

> Source: [Spenza](https://spenza.com/mvno/us-mvno-introduction/)

### Consumer Cellular (AT&T)

**Strategy:** Senior-focused niche with exceptional customer service

**Key Success Factors:**
- Clear target demographic (65+)
- AARP partnership for credibility
- Simplified plans (no complexity)
- US-based customer service
- Consistently ranked #1 in customer satisfaction

**Lesson:** "Consumer Cellular's focus on older adults demonstrates the power of specialization in the MVNO market. By tailoring their offerings to a specific group, they've built a loyal customer base and a strong reputation."

> Source: [No Jitter](https://www.nojitter.com/infrastructure/should-enterprises-use-an-mvno-such-as-cricket-or-mint-mobile-)

### Lively/Jitterbug (Verizon)

**Strategy:** Senior-focused with health/safety integration

**Key Differentiators:**
- Simplified phones (large buttons, easy UI)
- Urgent Response button (medical alert)
- Nurse On-Call premium feature
- AARP-endorsed

**Pricing:** Plans starting at $19.99/month, devices at $19.99-$29.99 (discounted)

> Source: [The Senior List](https://www.theseniorlist.com/cell-phones/jitterbug/)

