### Unit Economics

**Per-Subscriber Economics:**
| Metric | Typical Range | Notes |
|--------|---------------|-------|
| ARPU (Revenue) | $20-$50/month | Depends on plan tier |
| Wholesale Cost (COGS) | 30-60% of ARPU | $9-$18 on $30 plan |
| Gross Margin | 40-70% | Higher at scale |
| Customer Support | $2-$6/subscriber | If outsourced |
| CAC (Customer Acquisition) | $50-$150 | Can be much higher |

**Break-Even Analysis:**
- Light MVNOs typically break even between **5,000-25,000 subscribers**
- At $30 ARPU with 40% margin ($12/sub): 10,000 subs = $120K/month gross
- Need volume to absorb fixed costs (platform, support, compliance)

> Source: [MVNO Index](https://mvno-index.com/how-to-create-a-financial-plan-for-your-mobile-brand-mvno-4/)

