## Lower-Barrier Alternatives

Given the high capital and expertise requirements, consider these alternatives first:

### Option 1: Affiliate/Referral Program

**What:** Partner with existing MVNOs, earn commissions for referrals

**Economics:**
- SIM activation: $5-$15 per SIM
- Top-ups: 1-5% of value
- No operational burden

**Examples:**
- Wraptel Affiliate Program
- Various MVNO referral programs

**Best For:** Testing market interest with zero risk

> Source: [Wraptel](https://www.wraptel.com/MVNO-Platform-Partners-and-resellers)

### Option 2: Branded Reseller

**What:** Minimal customization, essentially white-labeled existing service

**Investment:** $10K-$50K
**Time to Market:** 1-3 months
**Control:** Very limited (pricing, basic branding only)

**Best For:** Quick market entry with existing customer base

### Option 3: IoT/Enterprise Focus

**What:** Skip consumer market, focus on connected devices and business customers

**Why Consider:**
- Higher margins than consumer
- Less support-intensive
- Growing market (smart meters, connected cars, sensors)
- IoT MVNOs can offer multi-carrier switching

**Market Size:** IoT MVNO market growing rapidly with demand for remote/underserved connectivity

> Source: [Eseye](https://www.eseye.com/resources/iot-explained/mno-or-mvno-for-iot/)

### Option 4: MVNO-as-a-Service

**What:** Modern platforms that dramatically lower entry barriers

**Examples:**
- **iBASIS:** "Start your own branded MVNO without high upfront investment"
- **eSIM Go + Vodafone:** "Any organisation with a subscription model can provide mobile services via rapid, automated enablement without upfront risk, cost or commitment"
- **Spenza:** "Establish your MVNO for hundreds of dollars rather than millions"

> Sources: [iBASIS](https://ibasis.com/solutions/mvno-as-a-service/), [eSIM Go](https://esimgo.com/knowledge-hub/newsroom/esim-go-partners-with-vodafone-uk-to-remove-mvno-barriers-to-entry-for-businesses-of-all-sizes/)

