## Honest Assessment

### Pros

- Recurring revenue model (subscription)
- Growing market ($30B+ US, 7.5% CAGR)
- Technology differentiation possible via apps/services
- Could complement other ventures (Rent-a-Nerd tech support)
- Modern MVNE platforms reduce barriers significantly
- IoT segment offers higher margins

### Cons

- **Capital intensive:** Even "light" MVNO needs $100K-$400K+
- **Razor thin margins:** 20-40% gross, often negative net early
- **Highly competitive:** Saturated with well-funded players
- **Regulatory complexity:** FCC, state PUCs, E911, CALEA, etc.
- **Customer support burden:** Telecom customers expect 24/7
- **Not our expertise:** Steep learning curve in regulated industry
- **Existing players in senior niche:** Consumer Cellular, Lively already dominate

### Decision Framework

**Proceed with full MVNO IF:**
- [ ] Another venture creates significant brand/audience (50K+ engaged customers)
- [ ] Specific underserved niche is clearly identified and validated
- [ ] Capital of $300K-$500K+ is available for proper launch
- [ ] Technical partner with telecom expertise is secured
- [ ] Regulatory counsel is engaged
- [ ] 3-year runway to profitability is acceptable

**Otherwise:** Start with affiliate/reseller model to test demand with zero risk

